@HeathieJ
I'm going to pick a sub-nit. There are certainly counting rhymes in English and, I suspect, in many other languages. The one I grew up with in English is, "One, two/Buckle my shoe./ Three, four/ Shut the door. /Five, six/Pick up sticks..." It doubled as a skipping-rope song.

But "2, 4, 6, 8..." is not a number-teaching song. It's generally used by children old enough to know their numbers already and it's not repetitive enough to reinforce the numbers. All the repetitions are around the names. I did like that all the numbers appeared phonetically but not orthographically in the grid. Nice.

@HeathieJ
