Both EMEND and AMEND make frequent enough appearances in the crossword that I always leave the first letter blank on the first pass, as do many other solvers, I'm sure. 

It could be considered what regular solvers call a "kealoa", so named because a clue such as [Mauna ___] could solve to either Kea or Loa. Best to keep an eye out for those!

